ica Fernandes]])\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|-\n|[[Asian Viewers Television Awards]]\n|Male Actor Of The Year\n|{{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2020\n| [[Kalakar Awards]]\n| Best Actor (Popular)\n| {{won}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodlife.com/photos/celeb-parth-samthaan/kalakar-awards-2020-parth-samthaan-and-monalisa-win-big-at-the-ceremony-1546698/|title=Kalakar Awards 2020: Parth Samthaan and Monalisa win big at the ceremony|website=www.bollywoodlife.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Lions Gold Awards]]\n| Best Actor (Critics)\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n\n* [[List of Indian television actors]] \n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|6955631}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Samthaan, Parth}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian male actors]]\n[[Category:Indian male television actors]]\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n", "name_user": "123.136.196.194", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parth_Samthaan"}
{"title_page": "Bank of Central African States", "text_new": "{{Infobox Central bank\n|bank_name_in_local = Banque des \u00c9tats de l'Afrique Centrale (BEAC) <small>{{in lang|fr}}</small>\n|image_1 = File:Bank of Central African States logo.png\n|image_title_1 = Logo of the BEAC\n|image_2 = Bank of Central African States 2014 front.JPG\n|image_title_2 = Headquarters of the BEAC\n|headquarters = [[Yaound\u00e9]], [[Cameroon]]\n|established = 1972\n|president =  Abbas Mahamat Tolli<ref>https://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=newsarchive&sid=aAI2ENyyHBrU</ref>\n|leader_title   = Governor\n|leader_title2 = Deputy Governor\n|leader_name2 =hh\n|bank_of = [[Economic and Monetary Community of Central Africa]]\n|currency = [[Central African CFA franc]]\n|currency_iso = XAF\n|reserves =\n|borrowing_rate =\n|deposit_rate =\n|website = [http://www.beac.int www.beac.int]\n|preceded = [[Banque Centrale des Etats de l'Afrique Equatoriale et du Cameroun]]\n|succeeded =\n|footnotes =\n}}\n\n[[File:Yaounde-BEAC.jpg|thumb|The Bank of Central African States with surrounding area.]]\n\n[[Image:CFA Franc map.svg|thumb|right|300px|BEAC is the central bank of the states in red.]]\nThe '''Bank of Central African States''' ({{lang-fr|Banque des \u00c9tats de l'Afrique Centrale}}, BEAC) is a [[central bank]] that serves six [[central Africa]]n countries which form the [[Economic and Monetary Community of Central Africa]]:\n\n*[[Cameroon]]\n*[[Central African Republic]]\n*[[Chad]]\n*[[Equatorial Guinea]]\n*[[Gabon]]\n*[[Republic of the Congo]]\n\nIn December 2010, a [[WikiLeaks]] memo dated July 7, 2009, said that Gabonese officials working for the Bank of Central African States stole [[US$]]36 million over a period of five years from the pooled reserves, giving much of the money to members of France's two main political parties.<ref>[http://english.aljazeera.net/news/africa/2010/12/2010122984115531832.html Gabon 'siphoned funds' to France] ''Al Jazeera''</ref>\n\n==Governors==\n[[Philibert Andzembe]] of [[Gabon]] was Governor of the [[BEAC]] from July 2007 until October 2009, when he was fired by the new president of Gabon, Ali Bongo, in response to a bank scandal in which $28.3 million went missing from the bank's Paris branch. [[Jean F\u00e9lix Mamalepot]], also from Gabon, was Governor for preceding 17 years.<ref>[http://www.grioo.com/info10860.html \"Le Gabonais Philibert Andzembe, nouveau gouverneur de la BEAC\"], Panapress (Grioo.com), July 6, 2007 {{in lang|fr}}.</ref>\n\n* [[Christian Joudiou]] (1973 - 1978) <ref name=\"bankgovernors\">{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100216125838/http://www.beac.int/histbeac.htm|title=Wayback Machine|date=February 16, 2010|website=web.archive.org}}</ref>\n* [[Casimir Oy\u00e9-Mba]] (1978 - 1990) <ref name=\"bankgovernors\" />\n* [[Jean-F\u00e9lix Mamalepot]] (1990 - April 2007) <ref name=\"bankgovernors\" />\n* [[Philibert Andzembe]] (July 2007- June 2008) <ref name=\"bankgovernors\" />\n*Lucas Abaga Nchama (2008- 2017)\n*[[Abbas Mahamat Tolli]] (2017 - to date) <ref name=\"bankgovernors\" />\n\n==See also==\n*[[Banque Centrale des \u00c9tats de l'Afrique de l'Ouest]] (BCEAO)\n*[[Central banks and currencies of Africa]]\n*[[CFA Franc]]\n*[[Central African CFA franc]]\n*[[Economy of Africa]]\n*[[Economy of the Central African Republic]]\n*[[Economy of Cameroon]]\n*[[Economy of Chad]]\n*[[Economy of the Republic of the Congo]]\n*[[Economy of Equatorial Guinea]]\n*[[Economy of Gabon]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Banks}}\n* {{in lang|fr}} [https://www.beac.int Official site of Banque des Etats de l'Afrique Centrale ]\n\n{{Central banks}}\n{{Central Bank by country}}\n\n[[Category:Central banks|Central African States]]\n[[Category:Economy of the Central African Republic]]\n[[Category:Economy of Cameroon]]\n[[Category:Economy of Chad]]\n[[Category:Economy of the Republic of the Congo]]\n[[Category:Economy of Equatorial Guinea]]\n[[Category:Economy of Gabon]]\n[[Category