{"title_page": "A Christmas Story Live!", "text_new": "{{short description|2017 live TV production inspired by the movie A Christmas Story}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name         = A Christmas Story Live!\n| image             = A_Christmas_Story_Live.png\n| caption           = \n| genre             = Musical\n| creator           = \n| based_on          = {{Plainlist|\n* ''[[In God We Trust: All Others Pay Cash]]'' (1966)\n* ''[[A Christmas Story]]'' (1983)\n* ''[[A Christmas Story: The Musical]]'' (2012)\n}}\n| developer         = \n| writer            = {{Plainlist|\n* Robert Cary\n* Jonathan Tolins\n}}\n| director          = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Scott Ellis]]\n* Alex Rudzinski}}\n| creative_director = \n| presenter         = \n| starring          = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Fred Armisen]]\n* [[Chris Diamantopoulos]]\n* [[Ana Gasteyer]]\n* [[David Alan Grier]]\n* [[Ken Jeong]]\n* [[Jane Krakowski]]\n* [[Maya Rudolph]]\n* Andy Walken\n}}\n| narrated = [[Matthew Broderick]]\n| composer = [[Pasek and Paul|Pasek & Paul]]\n| country            = [[United States]]\n| executive_producer = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Marc Platt (producer)|Marc Platt]]\n* Adam Siegel\n}}\n| producer           = {{Plainlist|\n* Robert Cary\n* Jonathan Tolins\n}}\n| editor             = \n| location           = [[Warner Bros. Studios]], [[Burbank, California]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/article/Ana-Gasteyer-Will-Join-Cast-of-Foxs-A-CHRISTMAS-STORY-LIVE-20171025 |title=Ana Gasteyer will join cast of Fox's A Christmas Story Live! |date=October 25, 2017 |work=BroadwayWorld |accessdate=December 2, 2017}}</ref>\n| cinematography     = \n| camera             = \n| runtime            = 180 minutes (with commercials)<br />133 minutes (without commercials)\n| budget             = \n| company            = {{Plainlist|\n* Marc Platt Productions\n* [[Warner Horizon Television]]\n}}\n| distributor        = \n| opentheme          = \n| channel            = [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]\n| picture_format     = \n| audio_format       = \n| first_aired        = {{start date|2017|12|17}}\n| last_aired = \n| website            = https://www.fox.com/a-christmas-story-live/\n| website_title      = Official Website\n| production_website = \n}}\n\n'''''A Christmas Story Live!''''' is a [[television special]]<ref>{{cite news |last=Keveney |first=Bill |work=[[USA Today]] |title=Behold the leg lamp: Fox's 'A Christmas Story' offers live-musical take on holiday classic |date=17 December 2017 |accessdate=13 May 2018 |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2017/12/14/christmas-story-live-fox-maya-rudolph-matthew-broderick/947183001/}}</ref> that was originally broadcast by [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] on December 17, 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.playbill.com/article/watch-this-first-glimpse-at-foxs-a-christmas-story-live |title=Watch This First Glimpse of Fox's A Christmas Story Live! |last=Fierberg |first=Ruthie |date=November 1, 2017 |website=Playbill |accessdate=November 1, 2017}}</ref> It was a live, televised musical remake of the 1983 film ''[[A Christmas Story]]'', and incorporated the 2012 stage musical version ''[[A Christmas Story: The Musical]]''. The live musical was executive produced by [[Marc Platt (producer)|Marc Platt]] and Adam Siegel, directed by [[Scott Ellis]] and Alex Rudzinski, and starred [[Matthew Broderick]], Andy Walken, [[Maya Rudolph]], [[Chris Diamantopoulos]], and [[Jane Krakowski]].\n\n==Premise==\n''A Christmas Story Live!'' is based on \"the short stories of humorist [[Jean Shepherd]] and is set in 1940s Indiana. It follows 9-year-old Ralphie Parker and his unrelenting desire to get his hands on a Red Ryder BB gun for Christmas.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Villarreal|first1=Yvonne|title=The leg lamp! The frozen pole! Fox prepares to bring a holiday classic to life with 'A Christmas Story Live!'|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/tv/la-et-st-christmas-story-live-20171216-story.html|website=Los Angeles Times|accessdate=18 December 2017|date=16 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Cast and characters==\n'''The Parker Family'''\n* [[Andy Walken]] as Ralphie Parker<ref name=\"ChildCast\">{{cite web|last1=Fierberg|first1=Ruthie|title=Meet the Kid Cast of A Christmas Story Live! {{!}} Playbill|url=http://www.playbill.com/article/meet-the-kid-cast-of-a-christmas-story-live|website=Playbill|accessdate=18 December 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n** [[Matthew Broderick]] as Ralphie (adult)<ref>{{cite news |url=https://ew.com/tv/2017/09/21/matthew-broderick-joins-foxs-a-christmas-story-live/ |title=Matthew Broderick joins Fox's A Christmas Story Live! |last=Agard |first=Chancellor |date=September 21, 2017 |work=EntertainmentWeekly |accessdate=November 1, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Maya Rudolph]] as Mother\n* [[Chris Diamantopoulos]] as The Old Man\n* Tyler Wladis as Randy Parker<ref name=\"ChildCast\"/>\n'''School characters'''\n* [[Jane Krakowski]] as Miss Shields\n* Sammy Ramirez as Schwartz<ref name=\"ChildCast\"/>\n* JJ Batteast as Flick<ref name=\"ChildCast\"/>\n* Sacha Carlson as Scut Farkus<ref name=\"ChildCast\"/>\n* Elie Samouhi as Grover Dill<ref name=\"AdditionalCast\">{{cite web|last1=Weigle|first1=Lauren|title='A Christmas Story Live' Cast List for FOX's Musical|url=http://heavy.com/entertainment/2017/12/a-christmas-story-live-cast-list-fox-musical/|website=Heavy.com|accessdate=18 December 2017|date=17 December 2017}}</ref>\n* Abigail Dylan Harrison as Louise<ref name=\"AdditionalCast\"/>\n* Artyon Celestine as Richie<ref name=\"AdditionalCast\"/>\n* Hayley Shukiar as Esther Jane\n'''Other'''\n* [[Ana Gasteyer]] as Mrs. Schwartz\n* [[Ken Jeong]] as Tree Salesman/Restaurant Owner\n* [[David Alan Grier]] as Mall Santa\n* [[Fred Armisen]] as Mall Elf<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lenker|first1=Maureen Lee|title='A Christmas Story Live': 5 things to look out for during the musical broadcast|url=https://ew.com/tv/2017/12/17/christmas-story-live-5-things-to-look-out-for/|website=EW.com|accessdate=18 December 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n* [[PRETTYMUCH]] as Hohman Indiana carolers\n\n==Musical numbers==\nTwo songs were created exclusively for the live broadcast that were not originally present in the original Broadway production including \"Count On Christmas,\" and \"In the Market for a Miracle.\"  In addition, three songs from the Broadway production were cut or reworked.  \"Overture\" and \"Parker Family Singalong\" were both cut, while \"Act One Finale\" was reworked as \"Ralphie's Nightmare.\"  The song \"Up on Santa's Lap\" was included in the television broadcast, but not included on the Christmas Story Live! album.<ref>{{cite web|title=A Christmas Story Live! by Various Artists on Apple Music|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/a-christmas-story-live/1324734885|website=iTunes.Apple.com|accessdate=24 December 2017|language=en-us|date=18 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n;Opening number\n* \"Count On Christmas\"{{efn|name=fn1|Song was written specifically for the television production.}} \u2013 [[Bebe Rexha]]\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n;Act I\n* \"It All Comes Down to Christmas\" \u2013 Ralphie, The Parkers and Ensemble\n* \"Red Ryder Carbine Action BB Gun\" \u2013 Ralphie and Jean\n* \"The Genius on Cleveland Street\" \u2013 The Old Man and Mother\n* \"When You're a Wimp\" \u2013 Kids\n* \"Ralphie to the Rescue\" \u2013 Ralphie, Miss Shields, The Parkers and Ensemble\n* \"What a Mother Does\" \u2013 Mother\n* \"A Major Award\" \u2013 The Old Man, Mother and Neighbors\n* \"Ralphie's Nightmare\"{{efn|name=fn1}} \u2013 The Parkers\n* \"In the Market for a Miracle\"{{efn|name=fn1}} \u2013 Mrs. Schwartz, Ralphie, Schwartz, Ensemble\n{{col-break}}\n\n;Act 2\n* \"Sticky Situation\" \u2013 Kids, Ensemble\n* \"You'll Shoot Your Eye Out\" \u2013 Miss Shields and Kids\n* \"When You're a Wimp (reprise)\" \u2013 Kids\n* \"Just Like That\" \u2013 Mother\n* \"At Higbee's\" \u2013 Elves\n* \"Up on Santa's Lap\" \u2013 Santa, Elves, Ralphie, Randy and Kids\n* \"Before the Old Man Comes Home\" \u2013 Ralphie and Randy\n* \"Somewhere Hovering Over Indiana\" \u2013 Ralphie, Randy and Kids\n* \"Red Rider (reprise #3)\" \u2013 Ralphie and The Old Man\n* Ralphie to the Rescue (reprise)\" \u2013 Ralphie and Ensemble\n* \"A Christmas Story\" \u2013 The Parkers and Full Company\n{{col-end}}\n{{notelist}}\n\n==Production==\nThe production was based on ''[[A Christmas Story: The Musical]]'', which in turn was based on the [[A Christmas Story|1983 film]]. [[Marc Platt (producer)|Marc Platt]] reprised his role as co-executive producer from the live television musical (2016) of ''[[Grease: Live]]'', joined by Adam Siegel, and television director Alex Rudzinski and theatrical director [[Scott Ellis]]. It was broadcast from the [[Warner Brothers Studios]] in [[Burbank, California]], primarily using outdoor sets. Ellis noted that emphasis on the \"feeling of family\" was an important aspect of the production, as \"it's not just razzle-dazzle stuff and big musical numbers. Our challenge is to never lose sight of the family aspect. And I think \u2014 I hope \u2014 we've succeeded in that.\" Songwriting duo [[Pasek and Paul|Pasek & Paul]], who wrote the songs for ''A Christmas Story: The Musical'', wrote three new songs for the production, including \"In the Market for a Miracle\" for Mrs. Schwartz, \"Ralphie's Nightmare\" for the Parker family, and the opening theme \"Count on Christmas\".<ref name=\"lat-xmasstorylive\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/tv/la-et-st-christmas-story-live-20171216-story.html|title=The leg lamp! The frozen pole! Fox prepares to bring a holiday classic to life with 'A Christmas Story Live!'|last=Villarreal|first=Yvonne|date=2017-12-16|work=Los Angeles Times|access-date=2017-12-18|language=en-US|issn=0458-3035}}</ref>\n\nPasek noted that the team had to try and maintain a balance between preserving the familiar and iconic aspects of the film, while also expanding upon it through its musical format. He explained that \"there are certain moments where we want to stay true to what people remember and then there's other moments where we have permission to do what only musical theater can do and turn the dad's fantasy into a tap dancing number.\" Platt remarked that when working on a project such as this, \"you prepare for the unknown. That's what makes live TV exciting. There are certain things that happen that you can't anticipate\".<ref name=\"lat-xmasstorylive\"/>\n\nUnlike previous years, [[NBC]] did not broadcast a live musical for the 2017 holiday season; while it did plan to produce a version of ''[[Bye Bye Birdie]]'' executive produced by and starring [[Jennifer Lopez]], it was delayed into 2018 (later delayed into 2019) to accommodate Lopez's schedule.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2017/12/14/christmas-story-live-fox-maya-rudolph-matthew-broderick/947183001/|title=Behold the leg lamp: Fox's 'A Christmas Story' offers live-musical take on holiday classic|work=USA Today|access-date=2017-12-18|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"lat-xmasstorylive\"/> The broadcast ultimately competed against [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]'s annual presentation of the film ''[[The Sound of Music (film)|The Sound of Music]]'', as well as NBC's ''[[NBC Sunday Night Football|Sunday Night Football]]'' between the [[Dallas Cowboys]] and [[Oakland Raiders]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://deadline.com/2017/12/cowboys-win-sunday-night-football-ratings-up-christmas-story-live-flounders-sound-of-music-movie-fox-nfl-nbc-1202229044/|title='Sunday Night Football' Ratings Up, Low 'Christmas Story Live!' Topped By 'Sound Of Music' Movie Encore In Viewers|last=Patten|first=Dominic|date=2017-12-18|work=Deadline|access-date=2017-12-18|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nDuring the special, Fox also broadcast a live, 2-and-a-half-minute commercial for ''[[The Greatest Showman]]'', a then-upcoming musical film that also featured songs written by Pasek and Paul. The spot, which was directed by [[Michael Gracey]] and [[Beth McCarthy-Miller]], and also simulcast on [[Facebook]], featured a performance of the number \"Come Alive\" with the film's stars [[Hugh Jackman]], [[Zac Efron]], [[Keala Settle]], and [[Zendaya]]. The presentation was billed as the first live television commercial for a film.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://deadline.com/2017/12/the-greatest-showman-hugh-jackman-zac-efron-zendaya-keala-settle-live-movie-trailer-a-christmas-story-1202228961/|title='The Greatest Showman' Live Movie Trailer Electrifies During 'A Christmas Story Live'|last=Ramos|first=Dino-Ray|date=2017-12-18|work=Deadline|access-date=2017-12-18|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.adweek.com/creativity/hugh-jackmans-live-ad-last-night-for-the-greatest-showman-was-quite-the-circus/|title=Hugh Jackman's Live Ad Last Night for The Greatest Showman Was Quite the Circus|work=Adweek|access-date=2017-12-18|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\n''A Christmas Story Live!'' received mixed to negative reviews, with the general audience reacting more harshly than professional critics.<ref>{{cite web|last1= Melas|first1=Chloe|title='A Christmas Story Live' didn't bring the holiday cheer|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/12/18/entertainment/a-christmas-story-bad-reviews/index.html|website=CNN|accessdate=18 December 2017}}</ref> On [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the production received a 46% rating based on 13 critics' reviews and 32% based on 56 audience reviews.<ref>https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/a_christmas_story_live/</ref> The show's three-hour length and musical numbers drew the most negative reactions, as Fox did not promote the program as a musical, and the lavish Broadway musical numbers were perceived to clash with the story's Midwestern setting.<ref>[https://www.usmagazine.com/entertainment/news/a-christmas-story-live-viewers-confused-by-musical-event-read-the-reactions/ A Christmas Story Live viewers confused by musical event: read the reactions]. ''Us Weekly''. Retrieved December 18, 2017.</ref> However, most of the individual actors' performances were positively received, as were the technical aspects of the special (such as scene and wardrobe changes).\n\nThe ''Los Angeles Times'' praised the performers: \"...Matthew Broderick, who found his own, gentler way through Shepherd's pointy prose...Maya Rudolph was affecting as Ralphie's mother, Chris Diamantopoulos gruff if less than epic as his father, the Old Man...Andy Walken was a good visual match for the movie's Peter Billingsley,...The whole company of kids, in fact, was energetic and on their marks,...\nSchwartz's mother, previously an offended voice on the other end of a phone call, was here gloriously embodied by Ana Gasteyer, who brought in a Hanukkah theme...\" but noted that \"...the virtues that have made the movie a seasonal perennial were somewhat swallowed by the narrative digressions and showstopping gestures of the musical.\"<ref>Lloyd, Robert. [https://latimes.com/entertainment/tv/la-et-st-a-christmas-story-live-review-20171217-story.html \"'A Christmas Story Live!' gets merry with Maya Rudolph and a winning Ralphie\"] \n''Los Angeles Times'', December 17, 2017</ref>\n\n===Ratings===\nThe overnight [[Nielsen ratings]] were a 2.8 rating/5 share with 4.52 million viewers,<ref>[http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tv-ratings-sunday-dec-17-2017/ \"TV Ratings Sunday Dec 17, 2017\"] zap2it.com</ref> as compared to the Fox network live telecast of ''Grease: Live'' in January 2016, which earned a 7.4 overnight and 12 million viewers.<ref>McPhee, Ryan. [http://www.playbill.com/article/a-christmas-story-live-ratings-up-against-football-fox-faces-numbers-dip-compared-to-grease# \" 'A Christmas Story Live!' Ratings: Up Against Football, Fox Faces Numbers Dip Compared to 'Grease'\"] Playbill, December 18, 2017</ref>\n\nFox [[rerun|reran]] ''A Christmas Story Live!'' in an edited two-hour time slot December 24, 2019. This telecast earned 1.11 million viewers, a 0.3 overnight rating and a 2 share.<ref>[https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tuesday-final-ratings-dec-24-2019/ Tuesday final ratings: Dec. 24, 2019]</ref> The rerun was also notable for going up against the original movie in the first airing of its annual [[marathon (media)|marathon]] on [[TBS (American TV channel)|TBS]]; the original drew more than twice the number of viewers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tuesday-cable-ratings-dec-24-2019/|title=Tuesday cable ratings: 'A Christmas Story' carries TBS to victory|work=TV By the Numbers|date=December 27, 2019|access-date=December 30, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Awards and nominations===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Award\n! scope=\"col\"| Category\n! Nominee(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\"|{{nowrap|[[70th Primetime Emmy Awards]]}}\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Original Music and Lyrics|Outstanding Original Music and Lyrics]]\n| [[Benj Pasek]] and [[Justin Paul]]<br />(for \"In the Market for a Miracle\")\n| {{nom}}\n|align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hipes |first1=Patrick |title=Emmy Nominations: 'Game Of Thrones, 'The Americans', 'Atlanta', Defending Champ 'Handmaid's Tale' Among Top Nominees |url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/2018-emmy-nominations-list-all-nominees-1202425072/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=July 12, 2018 |language=en |date=July 12, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Littleton |first1=Cynthia |title=Anthony Bourdain, 'Jesus Christ Superstar' and 'Saturday Night Live' Win Big on Night 2 of Creative Arts Emmy Awards |url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/creative-arts-emmy-winners-anthony-bourdain-saturday-night-live-1202934301/ |website=Variety |accessdate=September 13, 2018 |date=September 9, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\"|[[Casting Society of America#Artios Awards|34th Artios Awards]]\n| Outstanding Achievement in Casting \u2013<br />Live Television Performance, Variety or Sketch Comedy\n|  Bernard Telsey, Tiffany Little Canfield,<br />Rachel Hoffman, & Rachel Dill (Associate) \n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web |last=Nordyke |first=Kimberly |title=Casting Society of America's Artios Awards: 'Green Book,' 'Vice' Among Winners |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/2019-casting-society-artios-award-winners-full-list-1173402 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=February 1, 2019 |date=January 31, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[2017 in American television]]\n* [[List of Christmas television specials]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|https://www.fox.com/a-christmas-story-live/}}\n* {{IMDb title|6881890}}\n\n{{A Christmas Story}}\n{{Fox Live}}\n{{Warner Bros. Theatre Ventures}}\n{{Warner Christmas films}}\n{{Portal bar|Music|Television|Theatre|United States}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Christmas Story Live!, A}}\n[[Category:2010s American television specials]]\n[[Category:2017 in American television]]\n[[Category:2017 television films]]\n[[Category:2017 television specials]]\n[[Category:American live television programs]]\n[[Category:Christmas television specials]]\n[[Category:December 2017 events in the United States]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Films based on musicals based on films]]\n[[Category:Films based on multiple works]]\n[[Category:Films based on works by Jean Shepherd]]\n[[Category:Films set in Indiana]]\n[[Category:Fox television specials]]\n[[Category:Musical television films]]\n[[Category:Musical television specials]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2017 live TV production inspired by the movie A Christmas Story}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name         = A Christmas Story Live!\n| image             = A_Christmas_Story_Live.png\n| caption           = \n| genre             = Musical\n| creator           = \n| based_on          = {{Plainlist|\n* ''[[In God We Trust: All Others Pay Cash]]'' (1966)\n* ''[[A Christmas Story]]'' (1983)\n* ''[[A Christmas Story: The Musical]]'' (2012)\n}}\n| developer         = \n| writer            = {{Plainlist|\n* Robert Cary\n* Jonathan Tolins\n}}\n| director          = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Scott Ellis]]\n* Alex Rudzinski}}\n| creative_director = \n| presenter         = \n| starring          = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Fred Armisen]]\n* [[Chris Diamantopoulos]]\n* [[Ana Gasteyer]]\n* [[David Alan Grier]]\n* [[Ken Jeong]]\n* [[Jane Krakowski]]\n* [[Maya Rudolph]]\n* Andy Walken\n}}\n| narrated = [[Matthew Broderick]]\n| composer = [[Pasek and Paul|Pasek & Paul]]\n| country            = [[United States]]\n| executive_producer = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Marc Platt (producer)|Marc Platt]]\n* Adam Siegel\n}}\n| producer           = {{Plainlist|\n* Robert Cary\n* Jonathan Tolins\n}}\n| editor             = \n| location           = [[Warner Bros. Studios]], [[Burbank, California]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/article/Ana-Gasteyer-Will-Join-Cast-of-Foxs-A-CHRISTMAS-STORY-LIVE-20171025 |title=Ana Gasteyer will join cast of Fox's A Christmas Story Live! |date=October 25, 2017 |work=BroadwayWorld |accessdate=December 2, 2017}}</ref>\n| cinematography     = \n| camera             = \n| runtime            = 180 minutes (with commercials)<br />133 minutes (without commercials)\n| budget             = \n| company            = {{Plainlist|\n* Marc Platt Productions\n* [[Warner Horizon Television]]\n}}\n| distributor        = \n| opentheme          = \n| channel            = [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]\n| picture_format     = \n| audio_format       = \n| first_aired        = {{start date|2017|12|17}}\n| last_aired = \n| website            = https://www.fox.com/a-christmas-story-live/\n| website_title      = Official Website\n| production_website = \n}}\n\n'''''A Christmas Story Live!''''' is a [[television special]]<ref>{{cite news |last=Keveney |first=Bill |work=[[USA Today]] |title=Behold the leg lamp: Fox's 'A Christmas Story' offers live-musical take on holiday classic |date=17 December 2017 |accessdate=13 May 2018 |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2017/12/14/christmas-story-live-fox-maya-rudolph-matthew-broderick/947183001/}}</ref> that was originally broadcast by [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] on December 17, 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.playbill.com/article/watch-this-first-glimpse-at-foxs-a-christmas-story-live |title=Watch This First Glimpse of Fox's A Christmas Story Live! |last=Fierberg |first=Ruthie |date=November 1, 2017 |website=Playbill |accessdate=November 1, 2017}}</ref> It was a live, televised musical remake of the 1983 film ''[[A Christmas Story]]'', and incorporated the 2012 stage musical version ''[[A Christmas Story: The Musical]]''. The live musical was executive produced by [[Marc Platt (producer)|Marc Platt]] and Adam Siegel, directed by [[Scott Ellis]] and Alex Rudzinski, and starred [[Matthew Broderick]], Andy Walken, [[Maya Rudolph]], [[Chris Diamantopoulos]], and [[Jane Krakowski]].\n\n==Premise==\n''A Christmas Story Live!'' is based on \"the short stories of humorist [[Jean Shepherd]] and is set in 1940s Indiana. It follows 9-year-old Ralphie Parker and his unrelenting desire to get his hands on a Red Ryder BB gun for Christmas.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Villarreal|first1=Yvonne|title=The leg lamp! The frozen pole! Fox prepares to bring a holiday classic to life with 'A Christmas Story Live!'|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/tv/la-et-st-christmas-story-live-20171216-story.html|website=Los Angeles Times|accessdate=18 December 2017|date=16 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Cast and characters==\n'''The Parker Family'''\n* [[Andy Walken]] as Ralphie Parker<ref name=\"ChildCast\">{{cite web|last1=Fierberg|first1=Ruthie|title=Meet the Kid Cast of A Christmas Story Live! {{!}} Playbill|url=http://www.playbill.com/article/meet-the-kid-cast-of-a-christmas-story-live|website=Playbill|accessdate=18 December 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n** [[Matthew Broderick]] as [[Jean Shepherd]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://ew.com/tv/2017/09/21/matthew-broderick-joins-foxs-a-christmas-story-live/ |title=Matthew Broderick joins Fox's A Christmas Story Live! |last=Agard |first=Chancellor |date=September 21, 2017 |work=EntertainmentWeekly |accessdate=November 1, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Maya Rudolph]] as Mother\n* [[Chris Diamantopoulos]] as The Old Man\n* Tyler Wladis as Randy Parker<ref name=\"ChildCast\"/>\n'''School characters'''\n* [[Jane Krakowski]] as Miss Shields\n* Sammy Ramirez as Schwartz<ref name=\"ChildCast\"/>\n* JJ Batteast as Flick<ref name=\"ChildCast\"/>\n* Sacha Carlson as Scut Farkus<ref name=\"ChildCast\"/>\n* Elie Samouhi as Grover Dill<ref name=\"AdditionalCast\">{{cite web|last1=Weigle|first1=Lauren|title='A Christmas Story Live' Cast List for FOX's Musical|url=http://heavy.com/entertainment/2017/12/a-christmas-story-live-cast-list-fox-musical/|website=Heavy.com|accessdate=18 December 2017|date=17 December 2017}}</ref>\n* Abigail Dylan Harrison as Louise<ref name=\"AdditionalCast\"/>\n* Artyon Celestine as Richie<ref name=\"AdditionalCast\"/>\n* Hayley Shukiar as Esther Jane\n'''Other'''\n* [[Ana Gasteyer]] as Mrs. Schwartz\n* [[Ken Jeong]] as Tree Salesman/Restaurant Owner\n* [[David Alan Grier]] as Mall Santa\n* [[Fred Armisen]] as Mall Elf<ref>{{cite web|last1=Lenker|first1=Maureen Lee|title='A Christmas Story Live': 5 things to look out for during the musical broadcast|url=https://ew.com/tv/2017/12/17/christmas-story-live-5-things-to-look-out-for/|website=EW.com|accessdate=18 December 2017|language=en}}</ref>\n* [[PRETTYMUCH]] as Hohman Indiana carolers\n\n==Musical numbers==\nTwo songs were created exclusively for the live broadcast that were not originally present in the original Broadway production including \"Count On Christmas,\" and \"In the Market for a Miracle.\"  In addition, three songs from the Broadway production were cut or reworked.  \"Overture\" and \"Parker Family Singalong\" were both cut, while \"Act One Finale\" was reworked as \"Ralphie's Nightmare.\"  The song \"Up on Santa's Lap\" was included in the television broadcast, but not included on the Christmas Story Live! album.<ref>{{cite web|title=A Christmas Story Live! by Various Artists on Apple Music|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/a-christmas-story-live/1324734885|website=iTunes.Apple.com|accessdate=24 December 2017|language=en-us|date=18 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n;Opening number\n* \"Count On Christmas\"{{efn|name=fn1|Song was written specifically for the television production.}} \u2013 [[Bebe Rexha]]\n\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n;Act I\n* \"It All Comes Down to Christmas\" \u2013 Ralphie, The Parkers and Ensemble\n* \"Red Ryder Carbine Action BB Gun\" \u2013 Ralphie and Jean\n* \"The Genius on Cleveland Street\" \u2013 The Old Man and Mother\n* \"When You're a Wimp\" \u2013 Kids\n* \"Ralphie to the Rescue\" \u2013 Ralphie, Miss Shields, The Parkers and Ensemble\n* \"What a Mother Does\" \u2013 Mother\n* \"A Major Award\" \u2013 The Old Man, Mother and Neighbors\n* \"Ralphie's Nightmare\"{{efn|name=fn1}} \u2013 The Parkers\n* \"In the Market for a Miracle\"{{efn|name=fn1}} \u2013 Mrs. Schwartz, Ralphie, Schwartz, Ensemble\n{{col-break}}\n\n;Act 2\n* \"Sticky Situation\" \u2013 Kids, Ensemble\n* \"You'll Shoot Your Eye Out\" \u2013 Miss Shields and Kids\n* \"When You're a Wimp (reprise)\" \u2013 Kids\n* \"Just Like That\" \u2013 Mother\n* \"At Higbee's\" \u2013 Elves\n* \"Up on Santa's Lap\" \u2013 Santa, Elves, Ralphie, Randy and Kids\n* \"Before the Old Man Comes Home\" \u2013 Ralphie and Randy\n* \"Somewhere Hovering Over Indiana\" \u2013 Ralphie, Randy and Kids\n* \"Red Rider (reprise #3)\" \u2013 Ralphie and The Old Man\n* Ralphie to the Rescue (reprise)\" \u2013 Ralphie and Ensemble\n* \"A Christmas Story\" \u2013 The Parkers and Full Company\n{{col-end}}\n{{notelist}}\n\n==Production==\nThe production was based on ''[[A Christmas Story: The Musical]]'', which in turn was based on the [[A Christmas Story|1983 film]]. [[Marc Platt (producer)|Marc Platt]] reprised his role as co-executive producer from the live television musical (2016) of ''[[Grease: Live]]'', joined by Adam Siegel, and television director Alex Rudzinski and theatrical director [[Scott Ellis]]. It was broadcast from the [[Warner Brothers Studios]] in [[Burbank, California]], primarily using outdoor sets. Ellis noted that emphasis on the \"feeling of family\" was an important aspect of the production, as \"it's not just razzle-dazzle stuff and big musical numbers. Our challenge is to never lose sight of the family aspect. And I think \u2014 I hope \u2014 we've succeeded in that.\" Songwriting duo [[Pasek and Paul|Pasek & Paul]], who wrote the songs for ''A Christmas Story: The Musical'', wrote three new songs for the production, including \"In the Market for a Miracle\" for Mrs. Schwartz, \"Ralphie's Nightmare\" for the Parker family, and the opening theme \"Count on Christmas\".<ref name=\"lat-xmasstorylive\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/tv/la-et-st-christmas-story-live-20171216-story.html|title=The leg lamp! The frozen pole! Fox prepares to bring a holiday classic to life with 'A Christmas Story Live!'|last=Villarreal|first=Yvonne|date=2017-12-16|work=Los Angeles Times|access-date=2017-12-18|language=en-US|issn=0458-3035}}</ref>\n\nPasek noted that the team had to try and maintain a balance between preserving the familiar and iconic aspects of the film, while also expanding upon it through its musical format. He explained that \"there are certain moments where we want to stay true to what people remember and then there's other moments where we have permission to do what only musical theater can do and turn the dad's fantasy into a tap dancing number.\" Platt remarked that when working on a project such as this, \"you prepare for the unknown. That's what makes live TV exciting. There are certain things that happen that you can't anticipate\".<ref name=\"lat-xmasstorylive\"/>\n\nUnlike previous years, [[NBC]] did not broadcast a live musical for the 2017 holiday season; while it did plan to produce a version of ''[[Bye Bye Birdie]]'' executive produced by and starring [[Jennifer Lopez]], it was delayed into 2018 (later delayed into 2019) to accommodate Lopez's schedule.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/tv/2017/12/14/christmas-story-live-fox-maya-rudolph-matthew-broderick/947183001/|title=Behold the leg lamp: Fox's 'A Christmas Story' offers live-musical take on holiday classic|work=USA Today|access-date=2017-12-18|language=en}}</ref><ref name=\"lat-xmasstorylive\"/> The broadcast ultimately competed against [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]'s annual presentation of the film ''[[The Sound of Music (film)|The Sound of Music]]'', as well as NBC's ''[[NBC Sunday Night Football|Sunday Night Football]]'' between the [[Dallas Cowboys]] and [[Oakland Raiders]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://deadline.com/2017/12/cowboys-win-sunday-night-football-ratings-up-christmas-story-live-flounders-sound-of-music-movie-fox-nfl-nbc-1202229044/|title='Sunday Night Football' Ratings Up, Low 'Christmas Story Live!' Topped By 'Sound Of Music' Movie Encore In Viewers|last=Patten|first=Dominic|date=2017-12-18|work=Deadline|access-date=2017-12-18|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nDuring the special, Fox also broadcast a live, 2-and-a-half-minute commercial for ''[[The Greatest Showman]]'', a then-upcoming musical film that also featured songs written by Pasek and Paul. The spot, which was directed by [[Michael Gracey]] and [[Beth McCarthy-Miller]], and also simulcast on [[Facebook]], featured a performance of the number \"Come Alive\" with the film's stars [[Hugh Jackman]], [[Zac Efron]], [[Keala Settle]], and [[Zendaya]]. The presentation was billed as the first live television commercial for a film.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://deadline.com/2017/12/the-greatest-showman-hugh-jackman-zac-efron-zendaya-keala-settle-live-movie-trailer-a-christmas-story-1202228961/|title='The Greatest Showman' Live Movie Trailer Electrifies During 'A Christmas Story Live'|last=Ramos|first=Dino-Ray|date=2017-12-18|work=Deadline|access-date=2017-12-18|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.adweek.com/creativity/hugh-jackmans-live-ad-last-night-for-the-greatest-showman-was-quite-the-circus/|title=Hugh Jackman's Live Ad Last Night for The Greatest Showman Was Quite the Circus|work=Adweek|access-date=2017-12-18|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\n''A Christmas Story Live!'' received mixed to negative reviews, with the general audience reacting more harshly than professional critics.<ref>{{cite web|last1= Melas|first1=Chloe|title='A Christmas Story Live' didn't bring the holiday cheer|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/12/18/entertainment/a-christmas-story-bad-reviews/index.html|website=CNN|accessdate=18 December 2017}}</ref> On [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the production received a 46% rating based on 13 critics' reviews and 32% based on 56 audience reviews.<ref>https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/a_christmas_story_live/</ref> The show's three-hour length and musical numbers drew the most negative reactions, as Fox did not promote the program as a musical, and the lavish Broadway musical numbers were perceived to clash with the story's Midwestern setting.<ref>[https://www.usmagazine.com/entertainment/news/a-christmas-story-live-viewers-confused-by-musical-event-read-the-reactions/ A Christmas Story Live viewers confused by musical event: read the reactions]. ''Us Weekly''. Retrieved December 18, 2017.</ref> However, most of the individual actors' performances were positively received, as were the technical aspects of the special (such as scene and wardrobe changes).\n\nThe ''Los Angeles Times'' praised the performers: \"...Matthew Broderick, who found his own, gentler way through Shepherd's pointy prose...Maya Rudolph was affecting as Ralphie's mother, Chris Diamantopoulos gruff if less than epic as his father, the Old Man...Andy Walken was a good visual match for the movie's Peter Billingsley,...The whole company of kids, in fact, was energetic and on their marks,...\nSchwartz's mother, previously an offended voice on the other end of a phone call, was here gloriously embodied by Ana Gasteyer, who brought in a Hanukkah theme...\" but noted that \"...the virtues that have made the movie a seasonal perennial were somewhat swallowed by the narrative digressions and showstopping gestures of the musical.\"<ref>Lloyd, Robert. [https://latimes.com/entertainment/tv/la-et-st-a-christmas-story-live-review-20171217-story.html \"'A Christmas Story Live!' gets merry with Maya Rudolph and a winning Ralphie\"] \n''Los Angeles Times'', December 17, 2017</ref>\n\n===Ratings===\nThe overnight [[Nielsen ratings]] were a 2.8 rating/5 share with 4.52 million viewers,<ref>[http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tv-ratings-sunday-dec-17-2017/ \"TV Ratings Sunday Dec 17, 2017\"] zap2it.com</ref> as compared to the Fox network live telecast of ''Grease: Live'' in January 2016, which earned a 7.4 overnight and 12 million viewers.<ref>McPhee, Ryan. [http://www.playbill.com/article/a-christmas-story-live-ratings-up-against-football-fox-faces-numbers-dip-compared-to-grease# \" 'A Christmas Story Live!' Ratings: Up Against Football, Fox Faces Numbers Dip Compared to 'Grease'\"] Playbill, December 18, 2017</ref>\n\nFox [[rerun|reran]] ''A Christmas Story Live!'' in an edited two-hour time slot December 24, 2019. This telecast earned 1.11 million viewers, a 0.3 overnight rating and a 2 share.<ref>[https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tuesday-final-ratings-dec-24-2019/ Tuesday final ratings: Dec. 24, 2019]</ref> The rerun was also notable for going up against the original movie in the first airing of its annual [[marathon (media)|marathon]] on [[TBS (American TV channel)|TBS]]; the original drew more than twice the number of viewers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/tuesday-cable-ratings-dec-24-2019/|title=Tuesday cable ratings: 'A Christmas Story' carries TBS to victory|work=TV By the Numbers|date=December 27, 2019|access-date=December 30, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Awards and nominations===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Award\n! scope=\"col\"| Category\n! Nominee(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"| {{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\"|{{nowrap|[[70th Primetime Emmy Awards]]}}\n| [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Original Music and Lyrics|Outstanding Original Music and Lyrics]]\n| [[Benj Pasek]] and [[Justin Paul]]<br />(for \"In the Market for a Miracle\")\n| {{nom}}\n|align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hipes |first1=Patrick |title=Emmy Nominations: 'Game Of Thrones, 'The Americans', 'Atlanta', Defending Champ 'Handmaid's Tale' Among Top Nominees |url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/2018-emmy-nominations-list-all-nominees-1202425072/ |website=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=July 12, 2018 |language=en |date=July 12, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Littleton |first1=Cynthia |title=Anthony Bourdain, 'Jesus Christ Superstar' and 'Saturday Night Live' Win Big on Night 2 of Creative Arts Emmy Awards |url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/creative-arts-emmy-winners-anthony-bourdain-saturday-night-live-1202934301/ |website=Variety |accessdate=September 13, 2018 |date=September 9, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\"|[[Casting Society of America#Artios Awards|34th Artios Awards]]\n| Outstanding Achievement in Casting \u2013<br />Live Television Performance, Variety or Sketch Comedy\n|  Bernard Telsey, Tiffany Little Canfield,<br />Rachel Hoffman, & Rachel Dill (Associate) \n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web |last=Nordyke |first=Kimberly |title=Casting Society of America's Artios Awards: 'Green Book,' 'Vice' Among Winners |url=https://www.hollywood